contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionarypar|MLM|mlm}} '''MLM''' or '''mlm''' can be an abbreviation of: * [[Multipurpose Laboratory Module]], planned Russian module of the International Space Station * [[Multi-level marketing]] * [[General Francisco J. Mujica International Airport|Morelia International Airport]], IATA airport code MLM * [[Military Liaison Missions]], an American Cold War unit, in the Group of Soviet Forces, Germany * [[Millom railway station]], England; National Rail station code MLM * ''mlm'', a unit for [[luminous flux]], corresponding to 1/1000 [[lumen (unit)|lumen]] * [[Medical Logic Module]], a program written in the Arden Syntax computer language * [[Marxism–Leninism–Maoism]], a [[political philosophy]] derived from the ideas of [[Karl Marx]], [[Vladimir Lenin]], and [[Mao Zedong]]. In [[Roman Numerals]], '''MLM''' could mean [[1950]]. {{disambig}}
